quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"Does he not know that, when what is in the graves is turned upside down"
  100,10,and what is in the chests is exposed
  100,11,indeed their Master is well aware of them on that day
  101,1,The pounding disaster
  101,2,What is the pounding disaster
  101,3,And do you know what the pounding disaster is
  101,4,A day when the people become like scattered butterflies
  101,5,and the mountains become like fluffed up colored wool
  101,6,As for anyone whose balance (of good deeds) is heavy
  101,7,then he is in a pleasant life
  101,8,And as for anyone whose balance (of good deeds) is light
  101,9,then his residence is a bottomless pit
  101,10,And you don't even know what it is
  101,11,(It is) a scorching fire
  102,1,The competition for having more distracted you
  102,2,to a point that you visited the graves
  102,3,"No way, you will know"
  102,4,"And once more, no way, you will know"
  102,5,"No way, if you knew the sure knowledge (you would know that)"
  102,6,you shall see the hellfire
  102,7,then you shall see it with the sure eye
  102,8,"Then, on that day, you shall be questioned about the pleasures (you had in life)"
  103,1,By the time (the ages)
  103,2,indeed the human being is in loss
  103,3,except those who believe and do good works and recommend one another to the truth and recommend one another to the patience (and perseverance)
  104,1,Woe to every slanderer and fault-finder
  104,2,The one who piles up wealth and keeps count of it
  104,3,thinking that his wealth (and possession) makes him immortal
  104,4,"No way, he shall be thrown into the crushing fire"
  104,5,And do you know what the crushing fire is
  104,6,(It is) burning fire of God
  104,7,which rises over (and overtakes) the hearts
  104,8,indeed it closes over them
  104,9,in extending columns
  105,1,Did you not see what your Master did to companions of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their plot go wrong
  105,3,and sent flocks of bird on them
  105,4,throwing stones of baked clay at them
  105,5,then He made them like chewed up straw
  106,1,For keeping/protection of the Quraish
  106,2,their keeping/protection for the winter and the summer journey
  106,3,so they should serve the Master of this house
  106,4,the One who fed them in hunger and made them safe from fear
  107,1,Did you see the one who denies the religion (or the judgment day)
  107,2,That is the one who pushes the orphan away
  107,3,and does not encourage feeding the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who perform mandatory prayer
  107,5,those who are forgetful of their mandatory prayer
  107,6,those who make a show (and pretend)
  107,7,and withhold the small kindnesses
  108,1,Indeed We gave you plenty
  108,2,So perform mandatory prayer and sacrifice for your Master
  108,3,"Indeed your hater, he is cut off (and is childless)"
  109,1,"Say: you the disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not serve what you serve
  109,3,and you are not servants of what I serve
  109,4,and I am not a servant of what you serve
  109,5,and you are not servants of what I serve
  109,6,your way of life (religion) for you and my way of life for me
  110,1,When God's help and the victory comes
  110,2,and you see the people entering into God's way of life in bunches
  110,3,glorify you Master with His praise and ask His forgiveness. Indeed He is acceptor of repentance
  111,1,"May Abu Lahab's both hands perish (or may Abu Lahab's power perish), and it perished"
  111,2,His wealth and what he earned was of no use to him
  111,3,He is going to enter (and burn in) a flaming fire
  111,4,"and (so is) his wife, carrier of the firewood"
  111,5,around her neck is a rope from palm fiber
  112,1,"Say: He is the One God"
  112,2,God is the eternal and the needless and the needed
  112,3,"He did not reproduce, and He was not born"
  112,4,and there is no one equal (or comparable) to Him
  113,1,"Say: I look for protection of the Master of the morning twilight"
  113,2,from the harm of whatever He created
  113,3,and from the harm of darkness when it comes
  113,4,and from the harm of the blowers into the knots (who practices witchcraft)
  113,5,and from the harm of an envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say: I look for protection of the Master of the people"
  114,2,king of the people
  114,3,god of the people
  114,4,from the harm of the withdrawing tempter (who withdraws at the mention of God)
  114,5,the one who tempts in the people's hearts
  114,6,(whether) from the Jinn or the people